	)
	(text "We use the Pi Pico dev board instead of the RP2040 IC so in the\nfuture, we will have more flexibility and encapsulation if\nwe wanted to replace the Pico with another COTS or custom\nmicrocontroller development board."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 179.578 134.366 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "7c8ba1e1-12f8-4f7e-8172-ab587029dc2b")
	)
	(text "The Raspberry Pi Pico features the RP2040 dual-core ARM\nCortex-M0+ running up to 133 MHz, with 264 KB SRAM, 2 MB\nonboard flash, and flexible GPIO including ADC, PWM, I2C,\nSPI, and UART support, and is programmable in MicroPython."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 174.752 42.672 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "e50057e0-992c-4501-b5ce-b25ab1abc5aa")
	)
